{SPOTS SURVEY (contd)}
The Empire Pool (178/759) was built in 1958 when Cardiff staged the Commonwealth Games. 80% of the people said they had been there and one in three said they attended regularly.
Three in every four people said they watched sport on television, a half watch it often. Most people enjoyed a wide range of sports but the most popular were Rugby and Football, followed closely by Tennis and Athletics. Hobbies varied with age from sewing, knitting and reading to jogging and dancing. When asked which building their area required most, the young people said a Disco or an Ice Rink; while most of the adults said a Theatre or a Cinema.
